Add selective Playwright end-to-end tests for critical user journeys to ensure the full application stack works correctly.

## Overview
Playwright tests the entire application stack including UI rendering. Use sparingly - only for critical user journeys (5-10 tests).

## Setup

Create new test project: tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/
- Add Microsoft.Playwright.NUnit package
- Configure to start application before tests

## Critical Journeys to Test

1. Home page loads and displays projects list
2. Create new project workflow
3. View project detail with PR tree
4. Start Claude session and send message
5. GitHub sync completes successfully

## Test Pattern

```csharp
[Parallelizable(ParallelScope.Self)]
[TestFixture]
public class CriticalJourneysTests : PageTest
{
    [Test]
    public async Task HomePage_LoadsSuccessfully()
    {
        await Page.GotoAsync("https://localhost:5001");
        await Expect(Page.Locator("h1")).ToContainTextAsync("Projects");
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task CreateProject_AddsToList()
    {
        await Page.GotoAsync("https://localhost:5001");
        await Page.ClickAsync("text=New Project");
        await Page.FillAsync("input[name=name]", "Test Project");
        await Page.ClickAsync("text=Create");
        await Expect(Page.Locator("text=Test Project")).ToBeVisibleAsync();
    }
}
```

## Files to Create
- tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests.csproj
- tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/CriticalJourneysTests.cs

## Files to Modify
- Homespun.sln - Add new test project

## Notes
- Tests require running application
- Slower than API/unit tests - use sparingly
- May need to handle Blazor Server interactivity waits

## Verification
- Start app: dotnet run --project src/Homespun
- Run: dotnet test tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests
- All E2E tests should pass

